&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;BTIG seeks an experienced, high-performing Vice President to join the Corporate Access team in New York. This role blends strategic client engagement with hands-on event execution, ensuring best-in-class experiences for institutional investor clients, corporate management teams, and internal stakeholders. The ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced environment, is highly organized and detail-oriented, and brings strong judgment, discretion, and relationship management skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties &amp;amp; Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Partner with the Head of Corporate Access to develop and execute corporate access strategy, client engagement plans, and growth initiatives across key U.S. regions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver proactive, high-touch corporate access coverage to institutional clients and internal partners, ensuring timely response, accuracy, and clear communication of outcomes and rationale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Corporate Communications, Franchise Sales, Equities, Fixed Income, Research, Investment Banking, Prime Brokerage, Business Development, and other stakeholders to align corporate access and event priorities with Firm objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a primary point of contact for internal stakeholders on event feasibility, timelines, budgets, and execution standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead planning and execution for roadshows, industry conferences, panels, seminars, private dinners, group events, sponsorship activations, and internal events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end logistics: venue sourcing, contracting, run-of-show, vendor management, A/V, travel coordination, speaker coordination, seating plans, and onsite execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm food and beverage menus and ensure a high-quality attendee experience consistent with BTIG standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and manage the events calendar, budgets, and post-event reporting (attendance, feedback, ROI/impact observations, reconciliation).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce post-event wrap-ups including final attendee lists, budget closeout, survey insights, and recommendations for future programming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Corporate Communications to ensure BTIG branding across invitations, signage, press-related materials (as applicable), badges, banners, and marketing collateral.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage marketing/event inventory (e.g., signage, supplies, printed materials) to ensure readiness and consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal origination efforts by identifying high-impact event and access opportunities and helping build/maintain senior-level external relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and apply the connection between hospitality, experience design, and client development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements &amp;amp; Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Bachelor’s degree required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;5-7 years of relevant experience in Corporate Access, institutional client engagement, event strategy/production, or a related financial services environment (experience level flexible based on demonstrated scope and impact).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Demonstrated knowledge of corporate access best practices, industry trends, and institutional client expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Exceptional attention to detail, organization, follow-through, and discretion; sound judgment in time-sensitive situations.&lt;/

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;BTIG seeks an Analyst or Associate to support the Equity Research team in the Consumer space in New York. This individual will be responsible for assisting Senior Analyst in covering Consumer focused companies. The main concentration of this role will be conducting primary research, including financial analysis, due diligence on industry trends, company management and strategies. The ideal candidate will be a self-starter, highly motivated and hard-working individual.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties &amp;amp; Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Prepare financial models for use in analysis, company updates and recommendations for clients&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Keep senior analysts abreast of daily news flow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Conduct industry and company specific research through surveys, polling with physicians, speaking with Key Opinion Leaders, and other primary data collection methods for use in research reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Assist in writing comprehensive reports on research ideas; investment themes, data analysis; industry/company breaking news; and initiations of coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;As associates develop, they will maintain relationships with company management teams; industry contacts; internal sales and trading personnel; and institutional investors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements &amp;amp; Qualifications:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;2-4 years of experience in investment banking or equity research preferred&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Strong work ethic, resourcefulness, and the ability to think critically and creatively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Ability to create and maintain financial models and forecasts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Demonstrated interest in the sector&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Solid work ethic and superior attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Series SIE, 63, 86 &amp;amp; 87 licensing preferred, but not required upon hiring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
